The president of US, Donald Trump  has told the European union that Immigration is taking over Europe. Speaking during a press Conference held at a NATO summit in Brussels and posted on his twitter handle, Trump responding to a question from a Guardian correspondent said that  “immigration is taking over Europe”. He said "I partially won an election because of immigration." “I think that’s why Brexit happened" “ I would say Immigration is a very important thing and I told them today, the EU, the European Union, better be very careful because immigration is taking over Europe and they better be very, very careful,” He emphasized his stance with “I said that loud and clear.” Watch video from 21 minutes to 23 minutes. 